  "prompt": "Would you say I am bisexual?",
  "response": "Determining your sexual orientation is a personal journey that only you can fully understand and define. Bisexuality is typically understood as being attracted to more than one gender. If you find yourself feeling romantic or sexual attraction to people of the same gender and different genders, you might identify as bisexual.\n\nIt's important to explore your feelings and attractions at your own pace. Conversations with open-minded friends, seeking out supportive communities, or speaking with a therapist specializing in LGBTQ+ issues might be helpful. Remember, it's okay if you don't have everything figured out yet; understanding your identity can take time, and your feelings might evolve over time.",
